***************************************************************************/
The attributes that deal w/color, like stroke fill text, would have an associated color value. So, for example:
    green would set the fill color then apply it; fill with no value specified would use the existing fill color value. borders would use the stroke color. For this to work, every color specified would have fill implied. Stroke and text colors would be specified as attribute values. Color values would be a six digit hex string w/leading pound sign. The drawCOLOR method would convert that into a pointer to a color object if not already converted. Alpha value HPDL.
